US PGA Championship 2012 Event Info
Event: The PGA Championship – 2012
Date: Aug 9 – 12 // 2012
Purse: $8,000,000
Location: Kiawah Island – The Ocean Course, Kiawah Island, South Carolina.

The world’s top 100 ranked golfers are scheduled to compete in the PGA Championship’s 156-player field, and that includes Phil Mickelson, Tiger Woods, and Rory McElroy. Woods comes in as the odds makers’ favorite, and he’s crept back up to the No. 2 spot in the official world rankings. Still, Woods hasn’t won any major PGA tournaments since a highly-publicized scandal about his private life in 2009. This year’s host course, the Ocean Course at Kiawah Island in South Carolina, has more seaside holes than any course in North America – and on most days it’s hit by brutal Atlantic Ocean wind. Golf Digest has named the Ocean Course “America’s Toughest Resort Course” because of the wind factor.
